==English==

===Adjective===
'''flabellate'''

#Having parts or segments that are flattened and lengthened on one side, such that they are long and narrow like a stack of butter knives or a deck of playing cards.

===Usage note===
This term is used to describe the [[antenna]]e of several kinds of beetles, where the last segments are shaped like a deck of cards.  Flabellate antennae are a form of clubbed, or [[clavate]] antennae.

